## Step 6: PBS and Backup Infrastructure

Proxmox Backup Server (PBS) is a vendor appliance — it runs the official Proxmox
ISO, not NixOS. It is a shared operational service and lives on the **management
network** (native/untagged VLAN), not on an environment VLAN. Its clients are
Proxmox nodes, not VMs. See architecture.md section 5.3.

### 6.1 Download and Upload PBS ISO

Download the official PBS ISO from Proxmox:

```bash
# Download PBS ISO (check https://www.proxmox.com/en/downloads for current version)
wget https://enterprise.proxmox.com/iso/{{ pbs.iso }}

# Upload to a Proxmox node
scp {{ pbs.iso }} root@{{ nodes[0].mgmt_ip }}:{{ proxmox.image_storage_path }}/
```

Or download via the Proxmox web UI: Datacenter → Storage → local → ISO Images → Download from URL.

- [ ] ISO `{{ pbs.iso }}` uploaded to Proxmox ISO storage

### 6.2 Deploy PBS VM

```bash
cd site/tofu
framework/scripts/tofu-wrapper.sh apply
```

This creates the PBS VM with the ISO attached as a CD-ROM.

- [ ] PBS VM created in Proxmox

### 6.3 Install PBS from ISO

Open the Proxmox web UI console for the PBS VM and boot from the ISO.

PBS is on the **management network** (no VLAN tag). Use the management subnet
settings, not a VLAN subnet:

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Target disk | vda |
| Hostname | pbs.{{ environments.prod.dns_domain }} |
| IP | {{ vms.pbs.ip }}/{{ management.subnet | cidr_prefix }} |
| Gateway | {{ management.gateway }} |
| DNS | {{ vms.dns1_prod.ip }}, {{ vms.dns2_prod.ip }} |

Set a root password and record it — this is the PBS admin credential.

- [ ] Installation complete, VM rebooted
- [ ] PBS web UI accessible at `https://{{ vms.pbs.ip }}:8007`

### 6.4 Detach ISO

After installation, update `site/tofu/main.tf` to set `iso_file = ""` for the PBS
module, then re-apply:

```bash
cd site/tofu
framework/scripts/tofu-wrapper.sh apply
```

- [ ] ISO detached from PBS VM

### 6.5 Store PBS Root Password in SOPS

Do NOT paste the password into any chat or log. Add it directly to SOPS:

```bash
sops --set '["pbs_root_password"] "<password>"' site/sops/secrets.yaml
git add site/sops/secrets.yaml
git commit -m "sops: add PBS root password"
```

### 6.6 Run PBS Configuration Script

The `configure-pbs.sh` script automates all remaining PBS configuration:
SSH key setup, NFS mount, datastore creation, retention policy, API token,
Proxmox storage registration, and backup jobs.

```bash
framework/scripts/configure-pbs.sh
```

- [ ] Script completes successfully

### 6.7 Verify PBS Configuration

```bash
framework/scripts/configure-pbs.sh --verify
```

- [ ] All checks pass

### 6.8 DHCP Reservation

PBS uses a static IP set during installation. Create a DHCP reservation on
the management network for `{{ vms.pbs.ip }}` → `{{ vms.pbs.mac }}` to prevent
conflicts, even though PBS uses a static IP internally.

- [ ] DHCP reservation created on management network

### 6.9 Vault Raft Snapshot Timer

The Vault NixOS image includes a systemd timer that runs at {{ pbs.raft_snapshot_schedule }}
(before the {{ pbs.backup_schedule }} backup window) to take a consistent Raft snapshot.

After rebuilding and redeploying the Vault image:

```bash
ssh root@<vault-ip> systemctl list-timers vault-raft-snapshot
```

- [ ] Timer active on vault-dev
- [ ] Timer active on vault-prod

### 6.10 SOPS Entries Checklist

- [ ] `pbs_root_password` added to SOPS
- [ ] `pbs_api_token` added to SOPS

### 6.11 Verification

```bash
# V6.1 — PBS accessible from all nodes (management network, no VLAN workarounds)
for node_ip in {{ nodes | map(attribute='mgmt_ip') | join(' ') }}; do
  ssh root@$node_ip ping -c 1 {{ vms.pbs.ip }}
done

# V6.2 — PBS API returns version info
curl -sk https://{{ vms.pbs.ip }}:8007/api2/json/version

# V6.3 — NFS datastore mounted
ssh root@{{ vms.pbs.ip }} df -h {{ pbs.datastore_mount }}

# V6.4 — Manual backup test
vzdump <vault-dev-vmid> --storage pbs-nas --mode snapshot --compress zstd

# V6.5 — No VLAN sub-interfaces on nodes (should all be "clean")
for node_ip in {{ nodes | map(attribute='mgmt_ip') | join(' ') }}; do
  ssh root@$node_ip ip link show vmbr0.10 2>/dev/null && echo "STALE" || echo "clean"
done

# V6.6 — Proxmox storage points to management IP
pvesh get /storage/pbs-nas --output-format json | jq .server

# V6.7 — Vault Raft snapshot timer active
ssh root@<vault-ip> systemctl list-timers vault-raft-snapshot
```

- [ ] V6.1: All nodes can reach PBS on management network
- [ ] V6.2: PBS API responds
- [ ] V6.3: NFS datastore mounted and healthy
- [ ] V6.4: Manual backup completes successfully
- [ ] V6.5: No stale VLAN sub-interfaces on nodes
- [ ] V6.6: Proxmox storage config uses management IP
- [ ] V6.7: Vault Raft snapshot timer active and functional
